oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: From Folk, to Hillbilly, to Country - What Next? - various interviews - Part 2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Excerpt from "From Folk, to Hillbilly, to Country - What Next?" thesis for Austin Peay college by Mary Biggs, includes interviews with Grant Turner, Dottie West, Bill Carlisle, and Jimmy C. Newman.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Test tones -- Grant Turner talks about the Ryman Auditorium -- Mary Biggs talks -- Grant Turner talks about the history of the Grand Ole Opry -- Grant Turner talks about Roy Acuff -- Biggs talks about Roy Acuff -- Turner talks about various members of the Grand Ole Opry over the years -- Turner talks about doing the Ernest Tubb show -- Biggs talks about Ernest Tubb -- Turner talks about Jim Reeves and his death -- Turner talks about Marty Robbins -- Biggs introduces Dottie West -- Dottie West talks about her early life and career -- West talks about Marty Robbins and Jim Reeves -- Biggs talks about her thesis project -- Bill Carlisle talks about his early life and career -- Carlisle talks about his favorite tunes and family -- Biggs talks about her favorite Carlisle Brother tunes -- Carlisle talks about his new music -- Carlisle talks about his children and grandchildren -- Biggs talks about her thesis project -- Biggs introduces Jimmy C. Newman -- Jimmy C. Newman talks about his early career -- Newman talks about the Grand Ole Opry -- Newman talks about new genres emerging within country music (incomplete)
